Cook onion and garlic in oil in hot skillet until onion is tender. Stir in chili powder, oregano, cumin and cayenne; cook 1 minute. Add turkey; stir in broth, beans, ketchup, raisins and apricots. Bring to boil; reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, 20 minutes. Serve garnished with sour cream, chopped avocado and cilantro, if desired.